write a python function to read from an excel spreadsheet.
import pandas as pd 

def read_excel(file): 
    data = pd.read_excel(file) 
    return data
```This function uses the `pandas` library in Python to read data from an Excel spreadsheet and returns it as a dataframe object. The file parameter can be either the full path of the Excel file or just its name if it's located in the current directory.```
